{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"64ce32cd-e01e-4e03-8c29-1926b8df8a2d","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will mark the test as skipped/ignored in test results and display your reason message in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"239168c3-bb16-4fce-953b-d0130ea93b29","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to look anything up.","outputTokens":218,"requestId":"BC21:33166:1C8A94F:1FAE077:69FA93D0"},"id":"b4cdb569-e204-4276-ae19-fa40a44565b1","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:05:26.341Z","parentId":"a2794c41-d9b7-4748-8c13-756c2a6e3945"}
